      "content": "A loud humming sound from your ac unit's fan, with blades that aren't spinning, could be a sign of a few things. It might be a case of the fan motor being stuck, the blades being jammed, or even a loose connection somewhere. Before you go out there to investigate, it's wise to check the power supply first. Make sure the unit is unplugged to avoid any electrical hazards. If you're comfortable with it, you can also check the fan blades for any visible obstructions or debris that might be causing the issue. Remember, safety first, so if you're unsure, it's best to call a professional.",
